d call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:75:    \"\"\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:79:    required_keys = {\"coveredCalls\", \"totalCalls\", \"coverageRatio\", \"breakdown\"}\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:656:    \"\"\"Format a single dynamic-access stats entry.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:658:        covered=stats[\"coveredCalls\"],\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:665:    \"\"\"Return True when stats has the expected dynamic-access entry shape.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:667:        key in stats for key in (\"coveredCalls\", \"totalCalls\", \"coverageRatio