gy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\nforge/docs/improve-library-coverage.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](dynamic-access-workflow.md) ·\nforge/docs/improve-library-coverage.md:9:Many already-supported libraries have low dynamic-access coverage — their\nforge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:6:\"\"\"Workflow entry point for improving dynamic-access coverage on an existing library.\nforge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:9:focuses solely on generating new tests to improve dynamic-access coverage.\nforge/ai_workflows/improve_library_coverage.py:71:        description=\"Improve dynamic-access coverage for an existing library version.\",\nforge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:4:Improve test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `{library}`.\nforge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:13:Progress since the previous dynamic-access report:\nforge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:16:Remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites for this class:\nforge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:23:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:4:> [Dynamic-access strategy](dynamic-access-strategy.md)\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:39:        DAReport[(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\")]\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:164:- **Required prompts**: `dynamic-access-iteration`.\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:167:- **Loop**: parses `dynamic-access-coverage.json`; iterates over classes with\nforge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:182:- **Required prompts**: `optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration`.\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:10:        \"coveredCalls\",\nforge/schemas/benchmark_run_metrics_schema.json:15:        \"coveredCalls\":