tempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:411:If the library has no dynamic access, the workflow falls back to the standard `basic_iterative` strategy automatically.\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\nforge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1768:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage from the stored run metrics stats block.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1784:    covered_calls = int(dynamic_access.get(\"coveredCalls\", 0) or 0)\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1798:    \"\"\"Resolve the dynamic-access coverage report path for a new-library issue.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1809:        \"dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1810:        \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1815:    \"\"\"Load dynamic-access coverage directly from the generated report as a fallback.\"\"\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1942:        \"Analyze the generated tests, metadata, stats, and dynamic-access report in this repository. \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1946:        \"- Explain briefly why dynamic-access coverage is missing or still very low.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1965:        f\"Automation completed for `{claimed_issue.issue_coordinates}`, but dynamic-access coverage remains \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1967:        \"This suggests the generated tests are not exercising the required dynamic-access paths well enough.\\n\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:1969:        \"- Inspect the generated tests and compare them with the dynamic-access report to find uncovered call sites.\\n\"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:2631:            pipeline_argv.append(\"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\")\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4537:        \"--keep-tests-without-dynamic-access\",\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4540:            \"Forwarded to the new-library pipeline. Keeps generated tests for dynamic-access \"\nforge/forge_metadata.py:4541:            \"strategies even when no dynamic-access coverage is added.\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:62:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:80:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:98:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:116:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:135:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:153:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:171:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:189:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:207:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:225:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:244:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:263:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:282:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:301:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:321:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:341:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:360:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:374:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs javac_iterative to fix compilation, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:381:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:402:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:422:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:423:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:455:    \"description\": \"Composite strategy: runs java_run_iterative to fix runtime failures, then improves dynamic-access coverage.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:462:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:512:    \"description\": \"Pi bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:517:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:530:    \"description\": \"Codex bulk dynamic-access strategy. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, which iterates through uncovered classes and refines coverage class by class, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:535:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:548:    \"description\": \"Pi graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:553:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:567:    \"description\": \"Codex graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:572:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:592:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:593:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:614:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:615:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:636:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:637:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:658:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:659:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:697:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:715:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:728:    \"description\": \"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\",\nforge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:733:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\nforge/git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py:73:This PR improves dynamic-access coverage for {coordinates} by generating additional tests.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` — badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\ndocs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:75:    \"\"\"Return True when the dynamic-access stats entry matches the expected object shape.\"\"\"\nforge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:79:    required_keys = {\"coveredCalls\", \"totalCalls\", \"coverageRatio\", \"breakdown\"}\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:656:    \"\"\"Format a single dynamic-access stats entry.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:658:        covered=stats[\"coveredCalls\"],\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:665:    \"\"\"Return True when stats has the expected dynamic-access entry shape.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:667:        key in stats for key in (\"coveredCalls\", \"totalCalls\", \"coverageRatio\")\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:683:    \"\"\"Format the dynamic-access stats into a markdown section.\"\"\"\nforge/git_scripts/common_git.py:711:    \"\"\"Format a single version's stats (dynamic access + library coverage) into markdown.\"\"\"\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:327:- Generate dynamic access report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:328:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\ndocs/DEVELOPING.md:336:- Analyze external dynamic access: `./gradlew analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess --coordinates=group:artifact:version`\nforge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:4:> [Dynamic-access workflow](../docs/dynamic-acc