that require dynamic-access metadata, marked covered/uncovered. |\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:12:  - `_generate_dynamic_access_report(...)`: runs `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` and loads parsed report data from `dynamic-access-coverage.json`.\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:52:    Strategy->>Gradle: `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md:73:                Strategy->>Gradle: `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:39:        DAReport[(\"dynamic-access-coverage.json\")]\n./forge/docs/workflow-strategies.md:167:- **Loop**: parses `dynamic-access-coverage.json`; iterates over classes with\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:103:    Start([run begins]) --> Gen[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:149:    ReachedNT --> RegenReport[generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport]\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:180:A missing or unparsable `dynamic-access-coverage.json` after the initial\n./forge/docs/dynamic-access-workflow.md:274:| Reachability-repo Gradle tasks | `scaffold`, `populateArtifactURLs`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `test`, `nativeTest`, `generateMetadata`, `generateLibraryStats`. |\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:409:The `dynamic_access_iterative` workflow improves metadata accuracy by using the `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport` Gradle task to identify which dynamic-access call sites (reflection, JNI, resources, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:43:            \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:178:            \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:185:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:50:            \"dynamic-access-coverage.json\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:438:            \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:448:                \"cause=gradle_task_failed task=generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport exit_code={exit_code}\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:454:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:479:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/dynamic_access_iterative_strategy.py:510:                \"generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport\",\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:328:- Generate dynamic access coverage report: `./gradlew generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]`\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777669762465}]}
